# Environment Configuration

This example shows all available environment variables for the MCP Testing Framework.

## MCP Server Configuration

```bash
# MCP (Model Context Protocol) server base URL
# Default: http://localhost:4000
MCP_BASE_URL=http://localhost:4000
```

## Backend API Configuration

```bash
# Backend API base URL for the testing domain
# Default: http://localhost:5000
API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000
```

## Domain Configuration

```bash
# Specify which domain configuration to use
# Options:
#   - ./domain-configs/insurance.config.ts (default)
#   - ./domain-configs/healthcare.config.ts
#   - ./domain-configs/ecommerce.config.ts
#   - ./domain-configs/{custom-domain}.config.ts
#
# If not set, defaults to insurance domain
DOMAIN_CONFIG=./domain-configs/insurance.config.ts
```

## Test Configuration

```bash
# Jest test environment (usually 'node')
NODE_ENV=test

# Enable verbose test output
DEBUG=true

# Set test timeout (in milliseconds)
# Default: 5000
TEST_TIMEOUT=5000
```

## Usage Examples

### Using Default Configuration (Insurance Domain)

```bash
npm test
```

### Switch to Healthcare Domain

```bash
DOMAIN_CONFIG=./domain-configs/healthcare.config.ts npm test
```

### Switch to E-Commerce Domain

```bash
DOMAIN_CONFIG=./domain-configs/ecommerce.config.ts npm test
```

### Use Custom MCP Server

```bash
MCP_BASE_URL=http://my-server.com:3000 npm test
```

### Use Custom Backend API

```bash
API_BASE_URL=http://my-api.com:8080 npm test
```

### Full Custom Setup

```bash
MCP_BASE_URL=http://my-server.com:3000 \
API_BASE_URL=http://my-api.com:8080 \
DOMAIN_CONFIG=./domain-configs/healthcare.config.ts \
npm test
```

### Save to .env File

Create a `.env` file in the project root:

```env
# MCP Server
MCP_BASE_URL=http://localhost:4000

# Backend API
API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5000

# Domain Configuration
DOMAIN_CONFIG=./domain-configs/insurance.config.ts

# Test Configuration
NODE_ENV=test
DEBUG=false
TEST_TIMEOUT=5000
```

Then run tests normally:

```bash
npm test
```

## Notes

- If `DOMAIN_CONFIG` is not set, the framework defaults to the insurance domain
- Environment variables override .env file values
- All URLs should include protocol (http:// or https://)
- Port numbers should be explicit (e.g., :4000, not just 4000)
- Empty environment variables are treated as falsy
